        "body":  "Codex review note: needs one small correction before merge.\n\nThe functional change is narrow and CI is green, but the new `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` rationale for `rge-editor` is inaccurate. The PR-head comment says `rge-editor` embeds `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR` in launch logic and notes the gate does not run the editor binary. Current source falsifies that: `editor/rge-editor/src/main.rs` has `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` starting at line 1298, and all four `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR` uses are inside that test module at lines 1698, 1757, 1798, and 1844.\n\nPlease amend the comment to say `rge-editor` embeds the path in its in-crate test harness / fixture and golden-project paths, and that `cargo test --workspace --all-targets` compiles/runs those tests. In the same comment block, replace the remaining \"fixture-reading crates\" wording with \"path-embedding crates\" where it refers to the full `$bakingPkgs` list.\n\nI filed the matching handoff review packet: `ai_handoffs/GATE-STEP0-CLEAN-SET_REVIEW_2026-06-02_10-31-10+0300.md`.\r\n",
